OL,3,CStuck in hard mode? Why tricky video
OL,4,Cgames could be good for your mental
OL,5,Chealth
OL,7,FDespite early positive signs,
OL,8,Fresearchers believe more needs to be
OL,9,Fdone to paint a fuller picture of how
OL,10,Fvideo games impact player's brains.
OL,12,FOxford researcher, Dr Tamas Foldes
OL,13,Ftold ITV News: "Many studies,
OL,14,Fincluding systematic reviews and
OL,15,Frandomized controlled trials, have
OL,16,Fshown that video games can positively
OL,17,Faffect conditions like anxiety,
OL,18,Fdepression, PTSD, and ADHD.
OL,20,F"However, the field could greatly
OL,21,Fbenefit from improvements."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/14
